data.text:
Katie Martinez joined Mizzou Made Student-Athlete Development in January 2023.

Martinez's athletic experience began as she competed in Olympic Pistol at North Dakota State University where she competed yearly at the NCAA Collegiate nationals in Fort Benning, Georgia, and the Olympic Training Center in Colorado Springs, Colorado. For her professional experience she has navigated through student-athlete welfare through academic support and student-athlete development. As part of Mizzou Athletics, Martinez has built an individualized career readiness program that focuses on student-athletes navigating through the concepts of preparation, exposure and placement. Martinez has participated in several leadership development workshops through the NCAA and is DiSc facilitator certified and actively involved in NACDA.

Martinez is a South Dakota native and enjoys golfing, reading, and the company of her three canine companions, two huskies and a German shepherd.
